Any DeCal whose proposal has been submitted, approved by the chair, and whose facilitators/student-instructors have reached out to the dept scheduling staff will be listed at classes.berkeley.edu under CS 198 or EE 198. 

On the CS side, that is only one up until now but DeCal leaders have until Monday, July 6th to get completed proposals into the chair(s).  See https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/decal

Hi! The Web Design DeCal will definitely support remote learning - ever since classes went online this semester, we've been posting our lectures on YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/user/wddlive/) and will continue to do so in the fall! We also hosted online OH and already post all of our slides/labs online. Enrollment info will be available around the first week of the semester at our website, http://wdd.io/.
